    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's more than just being tired though. it feels like i've used up every single ounce of strength i had. like i'm just a hollow shell of a person and no matter how much \"help\" i get, the core of me is just... irreparable. is it even worth it to keep pretending there's a version of me that actually works?",
